ortant part of this beauty supply article to complete our makeup kit. Perfume is a spray used to give a pleasant smell to the body. A make up seems to be incomplete without a good perfume. Once again, there are a variety of perfumes for different occasions that you can get. Not all perfumes go well on every personality and you have to experiment with several of them to see which one suits your personality. There are many tips and advises about perfumes that I have covered in an article here. &lt;LINK&gt;', 'Beauty Supply That A Girl Should Have In Stock', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-08 23:33:00', '2016-03-08 23:33:00', '', 4, 'http://localhost:8080/femina/index.php/2016/03/08/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(8, 1, '2016-03-08 23:35:46', '2016-03-08 23:35:46', 'Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!', 'Hello world!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-08 23:35:46', '2016-03-08 23:35:46', '', 1, 'http://localhost:8080/femina/index.php/2016/03/08/1-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(9, 1, '2016-03-09 00:10:01', '2016-03-09 00:10:01', 'Looking pretty and attractive at a party is essential for every girl. For that, she needs to have a perfect make-up kit among other priorities. However, when choosing the beauty or make up products you should keep in mind the long term effects its going to cause on your skin. You should use the skin care products along with make-up products as a precautionary measure to reduce the chances of spoiling your skin. Also, while shopping at a store, some girls find it hard to pick products at the cosmetics section. In this article, I have created a list of beauty supply that a girl should have to complete her makeup and skin care kit.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, I will be writing articles progressively and posting them on this website to provide ladies with tips, tricks and guidance on how to properly use their makeup kits and use different cosmetics for different purposes like a pro. I will be comparing different products from all types of cosmetics from our beauty supply list so that the girls can make better choice on which product and brand to use or try.\r\n\r\nI will also be making efforts to find and recommend the right places, stores, companies or people to get the cheapest but good quality products for the users of this website so that they can afford to look attractive.\r\n\r\nYou can follow me on Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, Pinterest, Tumblr, etc.\r\n\r\n1. <strong>Cleanser</strong>\r\nA cleanser is used to wash away make-up, dirt, pollutants, oil and other impurities from the surface of the skin. Its a better alternative to bar soap and other skin cleansers because of various reasons such as, (i) skin pH is about 4.7 where as soap has a high pH between 9-10, which can imbalance the skin pH thus causing further growth of bacteria increasing acne, (ii) bar soap contains thickeners which clog up skin pores causing acne, and (iii) bar soap on the face removes natural oil which in turn causes sebaceous glands to overproduce oils causing acne. For these reasons, a facial cleanser is recommended instead of a soap to wash the face with. Usually, a cleanser is used as a part of skin care regimen in combination with a toner and a moisturizer.\r\n\r\nA cleanser is of utmost importance for the longevity of a healthy, acne-and-wrinkle-free skin along with some other anti-aging products especially if you put on heavy make-up very frequently.\r\n\r\nCleanser should be used twice a day, before and after sleep, because the skin gets affected from pollutants every day even within few hours and most cleansers are not harsh on skin.\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on cleansers, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of cleansers soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n2. <strong>Exfoliator</strong>\r\nAn exfoliator is basically like a soap or cream or lotion with granular particles in it which is applied or rubbed on the face and then washed off. It is used to remove dead and coarse skin cells from the face to make the skin smooth and soft.\r\n\r\nGentle or light exfoliator should be used once a day. However, since most exfoliators are not gentle, they should not be used more than once or twice a week.\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on exfoliators, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of exfoliators soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n3. <strong>Serum</strong>\r\n\r\nSerums are like moisturizers that provide active ingredients, antioxidants, hydrators and anti-inflammatories to the skin to keep it healthy and reduce its aging, wrinkles, and fine lines. Serums are quite concentrated and you have to be careful in using them, which I will cover in future articles. Serums are not necessary for a skin care regimen. However, if your skin has less problems, you have to wear less make-up to cover it up. Serums make your skin look healthier, radiant, younger and fresher. However, if you are suffering from Rosacea or eczema, you should avoid using a serum as it may cause aggravation.\r\n\r\nSerums should be used twice a day on regular basis. In the morning, the layer of sunscreen should be applied over the layer of serum, while at night a layer of moisturizer should be applied over the layer of serum.\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on serums, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of serums soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n4.<strong> Moisturizer</strong>\r\nMoisturizer is basically used to make the outer skin softer, smoother and more elastic, and to remove dryness through reducing evaporation. It contains natural or artificial oils, natural skin lipids and sterols, plant extracts, lubricants etc.\r\n\r\nMoisturizer should be used once or twice a day. But avoid using too much moisturizer at once as it could be more damaging than being healthy. Also, its important for you to know what type of ingredients your skin needs in a perfect moisturizer amongst the thousands that are available. Changing the type of moisturizer as your skin changes during various seasons of the year is also important. I have created another article to cover all such issues. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nSome of my favorite moisturizers are (i) Cetaphil Daily Moisturizer, which works well for me as well as many of my friends with normal or even excessively dry or super oily skin, and (ii) Aveeno Natural Radiance, which is not as good but has thinner constituency and so its absorbed into the skin quickly, and it does make the skin look radiant indeed.\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on moisturizers, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of moisturizers soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n5. <strong>Eye Cream</strong>\r\nSome people tend to not give special importance or any kind of priority to the skin surrounding the eyes. They feel that the other facial products will also take care of the eye skin. Besides, the eye creams are usually more expensive than other facial products. However, whether or not the eye cream fits in your budget, whether or not eye creams seem important to you, you should know a few things about why they exist at all.\r\n\r\nThe skin surrounding the eyes is more sensitive and fragile as compared to other areas, and its needs are totally different which regular facial products cannot fulfill. The skin around the eyes tends to age quicker, and is more prone to dryness and fatigue, thus forming dark circles easily. The eye cream is specifically designed to handle such issues by providing the area with proper elements that it needs most. You can find more in depth information here. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nWhether or not you want to focus on eye cream is upto you. However, if you do want it, you should use it once or twice a day. If you use once a day, use it at night.\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on eye creams, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of eye creams soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n6. <strong>Foundation Or Tinted Moisturizer</strong>\r\nSo far we were only discussing about the products for our skin care regimen. Foundation is the first actual product from our beauty supply kit (or our makeup kit :P). Foundation is a skin-tinting pigment used to cover skin flaws and create a uniform complexion, or to change the color-tone of natural complexion. Foundation can be liquid or powder. Liquid foundation can be dewy or matte, while powder foundation can be illuminating or matte. If you suffer from dry skin or rosacea, try avoiding the powder and go for liquid, because powder will affect your skin negatively in long run. If you have oily skin, try to avoid dewy finish using a mix of liquid and powder foundations. Visit here to get more detailed information on how to select and apply foundation. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nSome people have a misconception that tint-moisturizer is another skin care cream similar to other regular moisturizers or serums. However, when you match the ingredients of a foundation to those of a tint-moisturizer, you will notice striking similarities, such as use of solvent, mixtures of humectants and emollients, surfactants to keep the emulsion-type products mixed in a creamy base, ingredients to control the pH and thickness, skin toning pigments such as iron-oxide, titanium dioxide and mica, as well as preservatives to keep the product sanitized.\r\n\r\nSo a tint-moisturizer is basically a foundation. However, its a mild form of foundation since the amount of pigments used are usually less as compared to a foundation. Also, a tint-moisturizer hydrates skin better than a foundation due to higher concentration of humectants. Some brands’ foundation may act the same way as another brands’ tint-moisturizer though. So the two types of products vary a lot from brand to brand. You will have to figure out which type and brand works well for you depending on your preferences, skin type and season. But you definitely don’t need both products.\r\n\r\nIt should be obvious by now that tinted moisturizer shouldn’t be treated as a part of skin care regimen. Go here for more information about foundations and tinted moisturizers. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on foundations, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of foundations soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n7. <strong>Concealer</strong>\r\nWhile foundation is used to even out the skin tone across your face, concealer is used to hide zits, dark circles or scars. In some cases, foundation is able to hide what you are trying to hide, but if it doesn’t, use a concealer. Concealer usually goes on top of foundation, if both concealer and foundation are used. However, if you are not wearing any make up and just need to hide the marks, you can use just concealer without any layer of foundation.\r\n\r\nGo here for tips on how to use concealer like a professional. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on concealers, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of concealers soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n8. <strong>Blush and Bronzer</strong>\r\nBlush, also called rouge, is used to redden the cheeks. Bronzer gives a suntan appearance to the skin, and contours and highlights the cheekbone. Sometimes, the application of blush and bronzer can amazingly change the features of the face.\r\n\r\nBronzer is usually applied before blush. There are several different types of blushes and bronzers. Visit this &lt;LINK&gt; to find out more on how to pick the right one for your skin and how to apply them.\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on blushes, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of blushes soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n9. <strong>Eyeshadow and Eyeliner</strong>\r\nEye shadow is used to highlight or draw attention to the eyes, or to make them look attractive. It is applied on the upper eyelids, and sometimes even on the lower eyelids, and under the eyebrows. Different colors and different types of eye shadow provide difference look and feel. There are matte, liquid and shimmer and several other types. Shimmer is used for sexy look usually in parties, while matte is used for plain looks for more professional settings. Find out how to choose the right type of eyeshadow and how to apply them here. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nEyeliner is used to emphasize or change the shape of the eye. The difference between eye shadow and eyeliner is that eye shadow is used recreate and design the frame of the eye as well as to throw in some colors, whereas the eyeliner is used only to change the shape of the eye. Eyeliner is applied close to contours or rim of the eye, while the eye shadow is applied in more outer areas as well. You can use either an eyeshadow or eyeliner, or even a combination of both during your makeup depending on your preferences. Usually lighter eyeliners provide better and more open looks to the eyes. I have compiled another article to go deeper in this. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on eye shadows and eyeliners, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of eye shadows and liners soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n10. <strong>Mascara</strong>\r\nMascara is used for thickening, coloring, enhancing, curling or even lengthening the eyelashes. It comes in various forms primarily liquid, cream and cake (or powder). It is important to choose the right type of mascara for the right occasion and duration. Most mascaras come with an applicator, but since there are so many different types of applicators available for applying mascara on eyelashes, you can get a specific type according to your preference. Here is a detailed article on how to pick the right mascara and an applicator, and how to apply it on eyelashes. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on mascaras, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of mascaras soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n11. <strong>Brow Pencil</strong>\r\nA brow pencil is like a regular pencil with makeup instead of lead. It is used to enhance the shape of eyebrow, to thicken it, or to lengthen it, or broaden it up. Some people even remove or wax the entire eyebrows before drawing completely new ones from with the brow pencil, may be because they don’t like their eyebrows or may be they just want to try something new. Brow pencil comes in various types and colors. A pencil may have a thick end or a pointy end. Pointy-ended pencil is used to define details and outlines, while thick-ended pencil is used for applying makeup in large, base areas. In addition to the pencil, usually a brow pencil kit also contains tweezers to remove any stray hair, as well as a brow brush or comb to arrange the hair strands.\r\n\r\nHere is more detailed article on how to choose and use a brow pencil kit. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on brow pencils, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of eye creams soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n12. <strong>Lipstick and Lip Gloss</strong>\r\nLipstick is like a wax applied on lips to change their color and texture to make the face look more attractive. Some lipsticks provide protection to lips as well in a similar way as lip balms.\r\n\r\nLip gloss is used to provide a lustrous or shiny finish and sometime a subtle color to the lips. They can have various types of metallic, glittery, frosted or glossy finishes.\r\n\r\nLipstick is usually applied for parties as well as formal settings, while lip gloss generally for parties, weekends and late nights. There are many more points about lipsticks and lip gloss that need to be covered which you can find here. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on eye creams, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of eye creams soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n13. <strong>Nail Polish</strong>\r\n\r\nNail polish or paint is used to color the nails. Most of the time the terms nail polish and nail paint are used interchangeably, but some people prefer to call nail paint for the matte color while a nail polish for the lustrous or shiny color. This difference in terms is usually created by the brands and manufacturers. A nail paint gives an attractive look to the nails and is an important mark of makeup. Many women these days make creative designs on their nails using nail paints of different color instead of simply painting all the nails with one color. Since nail paints cannot be removed by simply by washing them, a special product called nail paint remover comes separate to assist with this task.\r\n\r\nI have covered nails in more detail here. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on eye creams, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of eye creams soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.\r\n\r\n14. <strong>Perfume</strong>\r\nPerfume is the last but most important part of this beauty supply article to complete our makeup kit. Perfume is a spray used to give a pleasant smell to the body. A make up seems to be incomplete without a good perfume. Once again, there are a variety of perfumes for different occasions that you can get. Not all perfumes go well on every personality and you have to experiment with several of them to see which one suits your personality. There are many tips and advises about perfumes that I have covered in an article here. &lt;LINK&gt;\r\n\r\nI will be covering more details on eye creams, tips and tutorials, and comparisons between different types of eye creams soon. Subscribe if you want to get notification on future articles.', 'Beauty Supply That A Girl Should Have In Stock', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-09 00:10:01', '2016-03-09 00:10:01', '', 4, 'http://localhost:8080/femina/index.php/2016/03/09/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
